-- Andy Pettitte Announces Retirement From Baseball After 16 Years, 5 Titles
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2011-02-04T15:42:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/andy-pettitte-announces-retirement-from-baseball-after-16-years-5-titles.html
  Andy Pettitte  announced his
retirement from baseball today, ending a 16-year pitching career
that produced a record number of postseason wins and five World
Series championships with the  New York Yankees .  Pettitte, a 38-year-old left-hander, formally said he was
stepping away from the game at a televised news conference at
Yankee Stadium in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  